<TITLE> Duty eased on sugar and dates ahead of Ramadan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 14 (bdnews24.com)The government has announced duty cuts on imports of sugar and dates, effective from Saturday, to bring down prices of the iftar staples ahead of Ramadan. A statement by the National Board of Revenue issued Friday said the current duty of Tk 4,000 per metric tonne on non-refined sugar has been withdrawn altogether. Refined sugar will see duty of Tk 7,000 per tonne cut to Tk 3,000. The government has also decided to withdraw the current 25 percent import duty and 5 percent regulatory duty on dates. The statement said duties are already exempted on other Ramadan staples such as lentils, onion and chickpeas. bd
